  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Administrative Support Executive",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a detail-oriented <strong>Operations Admin</strong> to support daily business operations and coordination tasks. This role is suitable for individuals who are organised, willing to learn, and comfortable working with basic systems and communication tools.</p><p>Training will be provided, and prior experience is not mandatory.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Assist with daily administrative and operational tasks</p></li><li><p>Coordinate schedules, documents, and internal records</p></li><li><p>Support communication with internal teams and partners</p></li><li><p>Handle data entry, reporting, and basic documentation</p></li><li><p>Follow up on tasks to ensure smooth operations</p></li><li><p>Perform ad-hoc duties as required</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Hiring only Singaporeans/PR & Minimum 18 years old</p></li><li><p>Able to communicate clearly in English</p></li><li><p>Basic computer skills (WhatsApp, email, Google Docs / Excel)</p></li><li><p>Willingness to learn and follow processes</p></li><li><p>Good attitude and responsibility towards work</p></li><li><p>Prior admin or operations experience is a plus, but not required</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Monthly salary between <strong>SGD 2,800 – 4,100</strong> (based on experience & performance)</p></li><li><p>Training and guidance provided</p></li><li><p>Career exposure to business operations and digital workflows</p></li><li><p>Supportive team environment</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow and take on more responsibility over time</p></li></ul><h3><strong>How to Apply</strong></h3><p>Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for a brief phone discussion to understand background and interest, followed by a detailed walkthrough of the role.</p>",
